		<div class="blog-header">
			<h2 class="blog-title">
					<a class="blog-title-link blog-link" href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/animal-farm-compared-to-my-family-by-gavin-high-4">Animal farm compared to my family By Gavin High (4)﻿</a>

			</h2>
			<p class="blog-date">
					<span class="date-text">
		5/15/2015
	</span>

			</p>
			<p class="blog-comments">
					<a href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/animal-farm-compared-to-my-family-by-gavin-high-4#comments" class="blog-link">
		0 Comments
	</a>

			</p>
		</div>
	
		<div class="blog-separator">&nbsp;</div>
	
		<div class="blog-content">
				<div><div class="wsite-multicol"><div class="wsite-multicol-table-wrap" style="margin:0 -15px;"> 	<table class="wsite-multicol-table"> 		<tbody class="wsite-multicol-tbody"> 			<tr class="wsite-multicol-tr"> 				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:49.999999999999%; padding:0 15px;"> 					 						  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:left"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/541174723.jpg?292" alt="Picture" style="width:292;max-width:100%" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%"></div> </div></div>   					 				</td>				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:49.999999999999%; padding:0 15px;"> 					 						  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:left"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/315280925.jpg?342" alt="Picture" style="width:342;max-width:100%" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%"></div> </div></div>   					 				</td>			</tr> 		</tbody> 	</table> </div></div></div>  <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(82, 79, 86);"><span style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(82, 79, 86);"><span style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(82, 79, 86);"><span style="font-style: normal; font-weight: 400;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;While reading </span><em><strong>Animal Farm</strong></em>, I began to see many parallels between the relationships of the animals on the farm and my relationships with my family. This first became apparent when Old Major began to use his wisdom and life experiences, to help educate younger animals and lead them in a positive direction. Due to his old age along with his extensive knowledge he is a comparable to my grandfather. Soon after Napoleon took over the farm I also begin to notice that the way he exercises his power is relatable to the way my parents use their authority to control me. On the other hand related strongly to the position of snowball on the farm. This most likely due his ability to stand up for his beliefs against Napoleon, &ldquo;a much more powerful and intimidating character than him&rdquo;. This trait is made clear when Snowball rebels Napoleon, in hopes of building &nbsp;a windmill despite the fact others were murdered for going against him. Similar scenarios often take place between my parents and I, For instance the constant discussion of whether or not i should receive my own car often becomes an argument within my house. Often demand that I will be able to run errands for my mom if i have my own car. However no matter what I say or do it will ultimately be up the them whether or not I receive a car, just like Napoleon having absolute power to prevent &nbsp;Snowball&rsquo;s windmill from being constructed. <br /></span></span></span><span style=""><span style=""></span></span><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><br /><span style=""></span><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>  <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;">&nbsp; &nbsp; M<span style="font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt; line-height: 115%; background-color: initial;">y younger sisters are easily comparable to squealer, due to their tendency to agree with my parents. Along with similarities between characters in the novel and my family members, I also noticed other similarities to modern day families in America. For instance Napoleon is reprehensive of the stereotypical father in America. Considering he has a he says goes mentality. The animals other than pigs may be compared to the younger generation as a whole. Due to their inexperienced and naive attitudes. Snowball however could be characterized as someone who can see what is wrong with society. His ability to question Napoleon and laws is similar to modern day Americans in favor of changing the&nbsp;discriminative and unfit laws against those of different sexual orientation. Clearly <strong style="font-style: italic;">Animal Farm</strong>&nbsp;is relatable to individual families and the United States as a whole.</span><br /><br /></div>

		</div>
	
	
