			<h2 class="blog-title">
					<a class="blog-title-link blog-link" href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/starting-riots-by-alyssa-7">starting Riots By: Alyssa (7)</a>

			</h2>
			<p class="blog-date">
					<span class="date-text">
		5/6/2015
	</span>

			</p>
			<p class="blog-comments">
					<a href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/starting-riots-by-alyssa-7#comments" class="blog-link">
		0 Comments
	</a>

			</p>
		</div>
	
		<div class="blog-separator">&nbsp;</div>
	
		<div class="blog-content">
				<div><div class="wsite-multicol"><div class="wsite-multicol-table-wrap" style="margin:0 -15px;"> 	<table class="wsite-multicol-table"> 		<tbody class="wsite-multicol-tbody"> 			<tr class="wsite-multicol-tr"> 				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:43.892617449664%; padding:0 15px;"> 					 						  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-thin " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:left"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/185448711.jpg" alt="Picture" style="width:auto;max-width:100%" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%"></div> </div></div>   					 				</td>				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:56.107382550336%; padding:0 15px;"> 					 						  <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); ">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); ">In today's society and the book <em>Animal Farm, </em>there are many similar themes within the book and today's events. One of these themes would be a corrupted leadership. In the book, Napoleon is a dictator and his opinion and only his opinion matters. Things on Animal farm are run one way and one way only. That is similar to what is happening just a few hours away in the city of Baltimore.<br /></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); ">Currently in Baltimore, Maryland, there is a riot amongst the streets due to the death of Freddie Gray. One man started the riot leading others to follow. Soon after the riot began, the local CVS was on fire showing that what one man has done has corrupted others to make a statement in the city of Baltimore. In the book<em> Animal Farm</em>, Old Major came up with the idea to take over Manor Farm because of the unfair treatment that Farmer Jones provides to the animals.<br />&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); ">After the death of Old Major, the &nbsp;animals revolt against Farmer Jones and later on take over Manor Farm changing the name to Animal Farm. The theme of a corrupted leader occurs in both of these events. Just one person/ animal&rsquo;s actions can change a group&rsquo;s perspective in such a short period of time. These actions affect everyone that was/ was not originally on board to revolt. For example, in<em> Animal Farm</em>, Napoleon ran the farm as a dictatorship having the other animals believe that whatever he says goes. Similarly, during the start of the riot, the actions of one person dictated how the rest of the city would react causing burning of buildings, injuries, and police and National Guard assistance. In <em>Animal Farm</em> things did not get quite as severe as Baltimore, but when Old Major came up with the idea to revolt against Farmer Jones he did intend to have a huge riot to occur. However in both Baltimore and<em> Animal Farm</em>, the revolts ended into something bigger. These actions of revolt occurred because the people of Baltimore and of Animal farm wanted to stand up for something that they believe was right. In the case of the Animal Farm, the animals wanted to be treated better and have better lives in their opinion. Because of the actions of a corrupted leader, this caused an outcome that got way out of hand.&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.5; background-color: initial;">Similar to Baltimore, the people of the city revolted because they are standing up for something they believe in. The riot became very largely spread through the city and has gotten out of control. This is proving that corrupted leadership turns into a bad outcome.</span><br />The intentions of both the people of Baltimore and the animals of Animal Farm were to state a point. However, these revolts occurred due to a corrupted leadership. This common theme has/ was carried throughout both events.<br /><br />Comment_Lorenzo:</span></span><br /><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); ">Im just going to put a comment here. Deal with it. I agree completely with the idea that anyone can make a change in society. One of my favorite quotes from the Dalai Lama &nbsp;Today's youth seems to be more open to change, and radically new ideas<br /><br /><br /><br /></span></span></div>   					 				</td>			</tr> 		</tbody> 	</table> </div></div></div>  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-thin " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:center"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/450534180.jpg" alt="Picture" style="width:100%;max-width:960px" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%"></div> </div></div>

