	</div>	<div id="blog-post-737015550118413689" class="blog-post">
	
	
		<div class="blog-header">
			<h2 class="blog-title">
					<a class="blog-title-link blog-link" href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/glittering-animal-farm-and-reality-with-propaganda-by-nikki-pierson-4a">Glittering Animal farm and reality with propaganda by nikki P. 4a</a>

			</h2>
			<p class="blog-date">
					<span class="date-text">
		5/5/2015
	</span>

			</p>
			<p class="blog-comments">
					<a href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/glittering-animal-farm-and-reality-with-propaganda-by-nikki-pierson-4a#comments" class="blog-link">
		0 Comments
	</a>

			</p>
		</div>
	
		<div class="blog-separator">&nbsp;</div>
	
		<div class="blog-content">
				<span class='imgPusher' style='float:left;height:48px'></span><span style='display: table;z-index:10;width:373px;position:relative;float:left;max-width:100%;;clear:left;margin-top:20px;*margin-top:40px'><a><img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/1889782.jpg?355" style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 10px; border-width:1px;padding:3px; max-width:100%" alt="Picture" class="galleryImageBorder wsite-image" /></a><span style="display: table-caption; caption-side: bottom; font-size: 90%; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;" class="wsite-caption"></span></span> <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:justify;display:block;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propaganda" title="">Propaganda</a> as we know is everywhere now a days but who knew Animal Farm written by George Orwell in 1945 also be full of different types of propaganda. Seventy years have past yet you the same strategies are use to sway the opinion of an individual.<br /><br />Name calling is pretty self explanatory, it is the use of abusive language and insults. Animal Farm uses name calling as a tactic of propaganda when&nbsp;Napoleon calls Snowball a traitor and a criminal. Napoleon really just wants to be in control. He was willing to do anything for that power. Sometimes it seems like name calling is the easiest way. Like you don&rsquo;t really know how to express what you are truly feeling so you just say something that may not be entirely true to get the result you want. To this day name calling occurs all the time especially over social media. Just a few days ago on twitter @cle_84 tweeted at actress, Emma Stone, &ldquo;Emma Stone looks like and smells like cat piss.&rdquo; The person doesn&rsquo;t even know Emma Stone but they felt the need to publicly insult her. The reason was probably not even about but it&rsquo;s easier to attack someone over the internet than to face what is really happening in reality. &nbsp;<br /><br />Another type of propaganda used when Animal Farm would be &ldquo;card stacking&rdquo;. This is when one seeks to manipulate audience perception of an issue by emphasizing one side and repressing another. Within Animal Farm this occurs when Squealer lies to the animals about how much food the farm has; when in reality the farm has very little food. Squealer used this tactic to gain control of the animals. As we know the pigs were considered to be the most intelligent animals on the farm, so Squealer took this opportunity to be preeminent. This can easily relate to the <a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2015/04/the-baltimore-riots-that-didnt-happen/391931/" title="">riot</a> that is occurring in Baltimore right now. The press has chosen to make all the african americans look like the antagonist and highlighting the white people as the victims but in reality there are many blacks who aren&rsquo;t the enemy are actually helping the destruction that was occurring. <br /><br /><br /><span style="">Bandwagon is everywhere. It&rsquo;s because people really just want to feel like they fit in. Probably because it&rsquo;s easier than standing out and risk putting their real self out there. &nbsp;Within Animal Farm the whole revolution against humans was due to bandwagon. The whole concept of &lsquo;two legs are good fo</span><span style="">ur legs are bad&rsquo; encouraged the bandwagon the animals all got behind the idea. I feel as a good way to relate bandwagon to current day would be commericals. Advertising companies tend to use celebrities to endorse their products. For example, Proactive uses all type of celebrities including Adam Levine. As you watch the commercial, seeing amazing results after amazing results, it leads you to the conclusion that this product not only works, but it will change your life like it already has for so many other people, even a celebrity.</span><br /><span style="line-height: 1.5; background-color: initial;"><br /></span></div> <hr style="width:100%;clear:both;visibility:hidden;"></hr>  <div class="wsite-youtube" style="margin-bottom:10px;margin-top:10px;"><div class="wsite-youtube-wrapper wsite-youtube-size-auto wsite-youtube-align-left"> <div class="wsite-youtube-container">  <iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/tglJAHHwO58?wmode=opaque" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> </div> </div></div>  <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span style=""><span style="">All of these parallels between Animal Farm and current day is showing that as times evolve the basis still remains the same. </span></span></div>  <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span "font-size:12.0pt;line-height:200%;font-family:&quot;times="" roman&quot;,serif;="" color:black"="" style="">"Emma Stone." <em style="">Perez Hilton</em>. N.p., n.d. Web. 3 May 2015. &lt;http://i.perezhilton.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/emma-stone-jimmy-kimmel-mean-tweets__oPt.jpg&gt;.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span>  <span "font-size:12.0pt;line-height:200%;font-family:&quot;times="" roman&quot;,serif;="" color:black"="" style="">Orwell, George, and Patrick Tull. <em style="">Animal Farm</em>. Charlotte Hall: Recorded, 1987. Print.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span></div>

		</div>
	
	
