		<div class="blog-post-separator"></div>
	</div>	<div id="blog-post-922762829721755947" class="blog-post">
	
	
		<div class="blog-header">
			<h2 class="blog-title">
					<a class="blog-title-link blog-link" href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/capitalism-and-communism-under-the-influence-of-propaganda-chris-f">Capitalism and communism under the influence of propaganda- Chris F.</a>

			</h2>
			<p class="blog-date">
					<span class="date-text">
		5/4/2015
	</span>

			</p>
			<p class="blog-comments">
					<a href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/capitalism-and-communism-under-the-influence-of-propaganda-chris-f#comments" class="blog-link">
		1 Comment
	</a>

			</p>
		</div>
	
		<div class="blog-separator">&nbsp;</div>
	
		<div class="blog-content">
				<span class='imgPusher' style='float:left;height:0px'></span><span style='display: table;z-index:10;width:auto;position:relative;float:left;max-width:100%;;clear:left;margin-top:0px;*margin-top:0px'><a><img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/7389182_orig.jpg" style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 10px; border-width:1px;padding:3px; max-width:100%" alt="Picture" class="galleryImageBorder wsite-image" /></a><span style="display: table-caption; caption-side: bottom; font-size: 90%; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;" class="wsite-caption"></span></span> <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:justify;display:block;"><span style=""><br /><span style="">Animal Farm</span><span style="">, written by George Orwell, was a book written in the middle of the cold war, where Russia&rsquo;s communist system was failing and flailing. And while the infamous novel captured near perfectly the corruption in the cogs and gears deep inside Russia, the novel </span><span style="">Feed </span><span style="">by M.T. Anderson predicts how the capitalist state in the United States could collapse with scary accuracy</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">Feed</span><span style=""> was written in 2002 but has recently resurfaced in the media because its message has become more and more relevant as consumerism in America has grown and as corporations have begun to really take over. (It was republished in 2012.) It&rsquo;s focal point, the Feed, is a chip placed in the brains of young children that directly connects them to the Stream Feed: a sort-of internet on steroids. Through the Feed, you can watch movies, talk virtually, buy anything you could possibly need, and be directly advertised to by those same big corporations. And since everything down to the schools (where usage of the Feed and how to spend your money are taught, since anything you could ever want to know is available to you in less than a second) are owned by these absolutely massive corporations, they are in absolute control of the seventy three percent of Americans who have the chip in their brain. Sounds kinda like the present, huh? </span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">Well, minus the Feed.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">Except not really. M.T. Anderson said in an interview about his book that he intended for the Feed to symbolize propaganda and its control on the human mind. The &ldquo;character&rdquo;, if you will, of the feed symbolizes almost exactly what Squealer does in </span><span style="">Animal Farm</span><span style="">. Squealer&rsquo;s entire job is to brainwash all the animals on the farm into believing that there were no problems- that the country and communism were existing and that those &ldquo;outside problems&rdquo; like Snowball and the other farmers were but afterthoughts. The farm was safe and prosperous. Now if you compare this to </span><span style="">Feed</span><span style="">, (and even to the modern United States) you can very clearly see situations where people in power try to cover up their wrong doings. In the case of </span><span style="">Feed</span><span style="">, the president of the United States (President Trumbull) states that the lesions that begin appearing on everybody&rsquo;s bodies are &ldquo;Not a result of any manufacturing wrongdoings&rdquo; and that &ldquo;they will go away.&rdquo; (They don&rsquo;t) </span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">But so what? Big deal, right? Governments lie to their citizens all the time. Usually it's in the best interest of the citizens for the government to lie- similar to a parent telling a white lie about, say, Santa. </span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><span style="">And you&rsquo;d be right. It&rsquo;s not a huge deal until the rebellious equivalent of a UN forms to stop your country from destroying the world. Which is exactly what happens in Feed: the Global Alliance (headed in South America, where the pollution is so bad that people become consumed by black sludge waves and die en-masse) threatens all throughout the book of issuing total war on the States. Strangely enough, even though they can hear of the news, the 73% of citizens with a Feed seem to not even care a little. They are so overwhelmed with the advertisements being streamed into their brains, that they assume that their livelihoods. They believe any war, any threat, is insignificant. They, as citizens, are clearly, fully, 100%-fully safe from any measly global alliance.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">Right?</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">Now look at Animal Farm under the same circumstances. The Animals were never really overcome with fear of any other farms or farmers (except for when Squealer used the other farms as a fear tactic- but even at that it was to make the farm seem safer and more protected from the evils of the humans. Even when the animals end up fighting and losing a war on their own turf, they celebrate like&nbsp;they've&nbsp;won. The propaganda that is fed to them leads them to believe they are right, which in turn makes it even more wrong. </span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">So what does this mean about capitalism? Basically: it&rsquo;s just as broken. The big heads can get away with doing very much in almost every form of government. Not to say that the States are worse than Communist Russia, but it can happen to anything, anyone. Humans cannot handle power. We have over two thousand years of proof to support that, as not one system has lasted even a quarter of that time. </span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">And as for propaganda, it is the tool humans use for stealing. Stealing thoughts, stealing energy, stealing land. It exists in every facet of our lives in areas where you cannot even imagine. </span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">The takeaway I want people to have from this, the moral, if you will, is that we are surrounded by voices that cannot be supported. People can know how to talk but not govern. We are surrounded by propaganda and need to be careful, but also recognize that it can be used in our best interests. </span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span>CITATIONS:</span><br /><span style="">Anderson, M. T.&nbsp;</span><em style="">Feed</em><span style="">. 2nd ed. Somerville: Candlewick, 2012. Print.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="">Orwell, George,</span><em style="">&nbsp;Animal&nbsp;</em><em style="">Farm</em><span style="">, New York:&nbsp;Harcourt, Brace &amp; Co,1946. Print</span><span style=""><br /><br /><br /></span></div> <hr style="width:100%;clear:both;visibility:hidden;"></hr>  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:center"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/698659_orig.jpg" alt="Picture" style="width:auto;max-width:100%" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%"></div> </div></div>  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:center"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/3089746_orig.jpg" alt="Picture" style="width:auto;max-width:100%" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%"></div> </div></div>

		</div>
	
	
