	</div>	<div id="blog-post-111584702846598208" class="blog-post">
	
	
		<div class="blog-header">
			<h2 class="blog-title">
					<a class="blog-title-link blog-link" href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/high-school-or-animal-farm-by-lilah-pd-7">High-school or animal Farm? By lIlaH pd. 7</a>

			</h2>
			<p class="blog-date">
					<span class="date-text">
		5/4/2015
	</span>

			</p>
			<p class="blog-comments">
					<a href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/high-school-or-animal-farm-by-lilah-pd-7#comments" class="blog-link">
		0 Comments
	</a>

			</p>
		</div>
	
		<div class="blog-separator">&nbsp;</div>
	
		<div class="blog-content">
				<div><div class="wsite-multicol"><div class="wsite-multicol-table-wrap" style="margin:0 -15px;"> 	<table class="wsite-multicol-table"> 		<tbody class="wsite-multicol-tbody"> 			<tr class="wsite-multicol-tr"> 				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:96.241610738254%; padding:0 15px;"> 					 						  <span class='imgPusher' style='float:left;height:110px'></span><span style='display: table;z-index:10;width:240px;position:relative;float:left;max-width:100%;;clear:left;margin-top:20px;*margin-top:40px'><a><img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/4559306.jpg?222" style="margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 10px; border-width:1px;padding:3px; max-width:100%" alt="Picture" class="galleryImageBorder wsite-image" /></a><span style="display: table-caption; caption-side: bottom; font-size: 90%; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;" class="wsite-caption">http://www.glogster.com/media/4/30/72/10/30721016.jpg</span></span> <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:justify;display:block;"><span style=""><span style="">It's interesting that even though </span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animal_Farm" style="" title=""><span style="">Animal Farm</span></a><span style=""> was written almost 70 years ago it is extremely relevant to today's society, especially in teenagers. Teens are naive and easily manipulated by social media and their peers because they are afraid to stand out. These social standards restrict teens from being able to express themselves in appearance and actions in order to avoid being bullied.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">While you may not see any direct connections between the characters in the novel and teens, they are surprisingly similar. When Napoleon and Snowball immediately take charge of the animals once Mr. Jones is chased off the farm they aren't opposed by any other animals because they are too clueless to realize that the pigs are assuming a higher authoritative position (Orwell 37). This can also be seen in high-schools today among different social groups. "Popular" teens have influence over the rest of their peers, especially in fashion trends, and the peers will conform to these trends without question. </span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">Propaganda is a main factor of maintaining the pigs authority on animal farm. During Squealer's speech he primarily uses rhetorical questions to make the other animals feel guilty for being suspicious of the pigs taking all the apples and milk for themselves (Orwell 14). The guilt Squealer provoked in the other animals is like peer pressure among teens.&nbsp;</span></span><span style=""><span style=""><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychological_manipulation" style="" title=""> Guilt can be used to pressure teens into doing things against their own beliefs because it puts them in the wrong if they don't do what they're being asked</a>.&nbsp;</span></span><span style=""><span style=""><br /></span></span><br /><br /><span style=""><span style="">Another way teens pressure their peers into doing things is by having a group of people gang up on one person and scare them into doing what others want. You see this when Napoleon has his dogs chase Snowball off the farm (Orwell 21). These dogs are a parallel to bullies in high-school because they use violence to force Snowball off the farm just as bullies use violence to make the other person do as they are asked. </span></span><br /></div> <hr style="width:100%;clear:both;visibility:hidden;"></hr>  <span class='imgPusher' style='float:right;height:0px'></span><span style='display: table;z-index:10;width:auto;position:relative;float:right;max-width:100%;;clear:right;margin-top:0px;*margin-top:0px'><a><img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/9711902.jpg?250" style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 10px; border-width:0; max-width:100%" alt="Picture" class="galleryImageBorder wsite-image" /></a><span style="display: table-caption; caption-side: bottom; font-size: 90%; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;" class="wsite-caption">http://aubreydaniels.com/pmezine/sites/aubreydaniels.com.pmezine/files/Bullying.bmp</span></span> <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;display:block;">Citation<br /><br />Orwell, George.&nbsp;Animal Farm. New York: Penguin Group, 1946. Print<br /></div> <hr style="width:100%;clear:both;visibility:hidden;"></hr>   					 				</td>				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:3.7583892617449%; padding:0 15px;"> 					 						  <div class="wsite-spacer" style="height:50px;"></div>   					 				</td>			</tr> 		</tbody> 	</table> </div></div></div>

		</div>
	
	
			<div class="blog-social  ">
		<div class="blog-social-item blog-fb-like"><fb:like href="http://mackayenglish.weebly.com/1/post/2015/05/high-school-or-animal-farm-by-lilah-pd-7.html" width="90" layout="button_count" action="like" show_faces="false" share="false"></fb:like></div><div class="blog-social-item"><a class="twitter-share-button" href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http://mackayenglish.weebly.com/1/post/2015/05/high-school-or-animal-farm-by-lilah-pd-7.html" data-text="High-school or animal Farm? By lIlaH pd. 7 - 
	
	 	 	Lit Relevance:&amp;nbsp;Honors 10 English
	
	" data-count="horizontal"></a></div>
