	</div>	<div id="blog-post-101261103743055749" class="blog-post">
	
	
		<div class="blog-header">
			<h2 class="blog-title">
					<a class="blog-title-link blog-link" href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/animal-farm-vs-palestine-by-nicolette-7">Animal farm vs. palestine by nicolette (7)</a>

			</h2>
			<p class="blog-date">
					<span class="date-text">
		5/3/2015
	</span>

			</p>
			<p class="blog-comments">
					<a href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/animal-farm-vs-palestine-by-nicolette-7#comments" class="blog-link">
		3 Comments
	</a>

			</p>
		</div>
	
		<div class="blog-separator">&nbsp;</div>
	
		<div class="blog-content">
				<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span style='text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); '><span style="color: rgb(82, 79, 86); font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;"><span style="color: rgb(82, 79, 86); font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none;"><strong style="font-weight: normal;"><span style='color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;'>Animal Farm by George Orwell, can be compared to the <a title="" href="http://www.vox.com/cards/israel-palestine/intro">Palestinian conflict </a>which is still happening today. The history of the Palestine conflict starts with WWI, when Britain promised the land to both Arabs and Jews in exchange for military participation. After the war, Britain produced two documents promising the land to both groups. The Arabs and Jews should have appealed to Great Britain, but instead they fought each other. Decades later, this conflict still exists. In Animal Farm, Snowball is used as the scapegoat to take the blame off of Napoleon for the failures of the farm. Throughout the book Snowball is blamed for random misfortunes, the first destruction of the windmill and the human attack on the farm. Eventually the animals are told that he was never on their side at all, but a spy for Jones.</span><br /><span></span><br /><span></span><span style='color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;'> The animals start to lose comradery as other animals confess to crimes against Napoleon.This causes a divide between the classes of animals. The solution to the Palestinian issue was to divide the country into a Jewish and an Arab section. This has only been a temporary solution. On Animal Farm, the animals experience a divide as the pigs rise to power. The barn becomes below Napoleon and he then moves into the farm house. </span><br /><span></span><br /><span></span><span style='color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;'>The <a title="" href="http://www.merip.org/primer-palestine-israel-arab-israeli-conflict-new">fight in Palestine </a>started not just as an argument over land but the religious freedom of those who have worked honestly and been persecuted. The Arabs already occupied the land but the Jews also needed to escape religious persecution after the holocaust. In Animal Farm, the war that is raged between humans and animals is not simply over a plot of land. To the animals, this piece of land is the start to a future where those who have worked honestly can feel safe and escape the whip of humanity. It is important in both examples for the groups to have a place where a common factor unifies them. In these cases, religion or species. </span><br /><span></span><br /><span></span><span style='color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;'>The animals view old Major as a wise prophet who can help them on the road to freedom. It&rsquo;s him who has the vision of the animals being free to live comfortably and collect the fruit of their labors. The Jews believe that Palestine is their homeland because of the biblical promise made to Abraham and his descendents, along with the fact that it was the historical site of the Jewish kingdoms of Israel and Judea. The Arabs believe they should have the land because they have occupied it for hundreds of years. Also because Abraham&rsquo;s son, Ishmael is the forefather of Islam, therefore the land is for Arabs as well. The story of Animal Farm portrays humans as those who have a divine right to rule of animals. For example, one aspect that sets humans apart from animals are hands, the tools of manipulation. Along with their superior brain power. &nbsp;</span><br /><span></span><br /><span></span><span style='color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;'>Animal Farm and Palestine share a common goal because of the fact that they want to be free of persecution and slavery from &ldquo;superior&rdquo; groups. Their common mistake is that by the end they forget who the real enemy should be. The Jews and the Arabs fight each other instead the country that promised them both the land. The animals turn on each other instead of sticking with the common goal of expelling the humans and being independent.</span><br /><span></span><br /><span></span><br /><br /></strong></span></span></span></div>  <div><div class="wsite-multicol"><div class="wsite-multicol-table-wrap" style="margin:0 -15px;"> 	<table class="wsite-multicol-table"> 		<tbody class="wsite-multicol-tbody"> 			<tr class="wsite-multicol-tr"> 				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:50%; padding:0 15px;"> 					 						  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:left"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/181066470.jpg?1430695981" alt="Picture" style="width:auto;max-width:100%" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%"></div> </div></div>   					 				</td>				<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width:50%; padding:0 15px;"> 					 						  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:center"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/646173289.png" alt="Picture" style="width:100%;max-width:432px" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%"></div> </div></div>   					 				</td>			</tr> 		</tbody> 	</table> </div></div></div>

		</div>
	
	
			<div class="blog-social  ">
		<div class="blog-social-item blog-fb-like"><fb:like href="http://mackayenglish.weebly.com/1/post/2015/05/animal-farm-vs-palestine-by-nicolette-7.html" width="90" layout="button_count" action="like" show_faces="false" share="false"></fb:like></div><div class="blog-social-item"><a class="twitter-share-button" href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http://mackayenglish.weebly.com/1/post/2015/05/animal-farm-vs-palestine-by-nicolette-7.html" data-text="Animal farm vs. palestine by nicolette (7) - 
	
	 	 	Lit Relevance:&amp;nbsp;Honors 10 English
	
	" data-count="horizontal"></a></div>
