	</div>	<div id="blog-post-969220384584577093" class="blog-post">
	
	
		<div class="blog-header">
			<h2 class="blog-title">
					<a class="blog-title-link blog-link" href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/north-koreas-farm-quentin4a">North korea's Farm Quentin(4A)</a>

			</h2>
			<p class="blog-date">
					<span class="date-text">
		5/3/2015
	</span>

			</p>
			<p class="blog-comments">
					<a href="//mackayenglish.weebly.com/blog/north-koreas-farm-quentin4a#comments" class="blog-link">
		6 Comments
	</a>

			</p>
		</div>
	
		<div class="blog-separator">&nbsp;</div>
	
		<div class="blog-content">
				<div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span style='text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); '><br /><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style="">Fear, Loyalty, and Control. Some of the many words that link the conditions in North Korea to George Orwell&rsquo;s </span><span style="">Animal Farm.</span><span style=""> The oppressed animals of Animal Farm, though not physically, resemble the citizens of North Korea.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style="">In a recent Documentary called Inside North Korea, a doctor went to Korea and performed 1,000 eye surgeries that removed cataracts to heal blindness. After each successful procedure, the patient would rush over to a painting of Kim Jong Un, or as they said, &ldquo;the Great Leader&rdquo;, and fall to their knees praising him. They would thank him for allowing them to see again. However, none of the patients uttered a single thanks to the doctor or his team despite the fact that only the doctor&rsquo;s operations allowed them to see. When interviewed, they said that is was only because of the Great Leader&rsquo;s generosity and guidance they were able to see again...and only because of his guidance and generosity.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">What a great guy.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "></span></span></div>  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:center"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/9348322_orig.png" alt="Picture" style="width:auto;max-width:100%" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%">Patients thanking Kim Jong Un after getting back their eyesight.</div> </div></div>  <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span style='text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); '><span style="">This is very similar to how the later generations of animals in </span><span style="">Animal Farm</span><span style="">  treat Napoleon. They give thanks to anything he has done and believe  that it was his personal grace and generosity that allowed them to drink  water or lay eggs. To any person who has read the novel, they know  Napoleon is manipulating them and it is not because of his &ldquo;generosity&rdquo;  that they were able to do everyday things. Unfortunately, the animals  are unaware of this act and proceed to treat him as a god.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">However,  these are not the only differences. Napoleon uses fear to control the  other animals on the farm. He makes examples of those who have confessed  to crimes they did not commit. He has them brutally murdered in front  of the whole farm. This destroys any feeling of rebellion towards  Napoleon.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style="">These  methods are not unlike those used by North Korea Dictator Kim Jong Un.  Whenever anyone, no matter rank or relationship, speaks out against him  or the North Korean Government, he has them executed in the most brutal  of manners. Most of the executed people are innocent have not done  anything wrong, but they are brought out in front of large crowds and  shot, hacked apart, or eaten by rabid dogs, but the last form is only a  rumor.</span><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "></span></span></div>  <div><div class="wsite-image wsite-image-border-none " style="padding-top:10px;padding-bottom:10px;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;text-align:center"> <a> <img src="/uploads/5/0/9/4/50940509/334684520.jpg" alt="Picture" style="width:auto;max-width:100%" /> </a> <div style="display:block;font-size:90%">North Korean guards walking a feral dog.</div> </div></div>  <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span style='text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); '><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><span style="text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); "><span style="">Another way that </span><span style="">Animal Farm</span><span style=""> is relatable to North Korea is the secret police. While they do not act publically, like the Napoleon&rsquo;s dogs in </span><span style="">Animal Farm</span><span style="">,  the Ministry of State Security(MSS) basically serves the same function.  They are primarily used to root out rebellion against Kim Jong Un or  the North Korean Government. They are ruthless and ensure that the will  of the Great Leader is carried out. They are also similar to Napoleon&rsquo;s  dogs in the way that they are eyes and ears of the Great Leader. based  on tales from defectors, one in every five households are members of the  MSS.</span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><br /><br /></span></span></span></div>  <div class="paragraph" style="text-align:left;"><span style='text-decoration:none; font-style:normal; font-weight:400; color:rgb(82, 79, 86); '>Picture Sources<br /><a style="" href="http://www.independent.co.uk/news/north-korean-defector-says-she-believed-kim-jongil-was-a-god-who-could-read-her-mind-9251983.html"><span style="">http://www.independent.co.uk/news/north-korean-defector-says-she-believed-kim-jongil-was-a-god-who-could-read-her-mind-9251983.html</span></a><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><a style="" href="http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/01/05/north-korea-s-monstrous-murder-methods.html"><span style="">http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2014/01/05/north-korea-s-monstrous-murder-methods.html</span></a><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><a style="" href="http://www.nknews.org/2014/02/neighborhood-watch-inside-north-koreas-secret-service-system/"><span style="">http://www.nknews.org/2014/02/neighborhood-watch-inside-north-koreas-secret-service-system/</span></a><br /><span style=""></span><br /><span style=""></span><a style="" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mxLBywKrTf4"><span style="">www.youtube.com/watch?v=mxLBywKrTf4<br />Animal Farm citation<br /></span></a><a style="" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mxLBywKrTf4">http://www.george-orwell.org/animal_farm/0.html<br /></a></span></div>

		</div>
	
	
			<div class="blog-social  ">
		<div class="blog-social-item blog-fb-like"><fb:like href="http://mackayenglish.weebly.com/1/post/2015/05/north-koreas-farm-quentin4a.html" width="90" layout="button_count" action="like" show_faces="false" share="false"></fb:like></div><div class="blog-social-item"><a class="twitter-share-button" href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http://mackayenglish.weebly.com/1/post/2015/05/north-koreas-farm-quentin4a.html" data-text="North korea&#039;s Farm Quentin(4A) - 
	
